<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>System Forge — Research Overview</title>
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=Space+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap');

  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --ink: #1a1a2e;
    --ink-light: #4a4a6a;
    --ink-faint: #9090aa;
    --bg: #f7f7f2;
    --bg-card: #ffffff;
    --accent: #2d6be4;
    --accent-light: #e8f0fd;
    --amber: #e8860a;
    --amber-light: #fef3e2;
    --green: #1a8a5a;
    --green-light: #e4f5ed;
    --purple: #6b3fa0;
    --purple-light: #f0eaf8;
    --rule: #e5e5e0;
    --tag-bg: #f0f0ea;
  }

  body {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding: 0;
  }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  .header {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: white;
    padding: 56px 64px 48px;
  }
  .header-label {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #6b7fc4;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .header h1 {
    font-size: 38px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    max-width: 620px;
  }
  .header h1 span { color: #7ba7f5; }
  .header p {
    color: #a0a8cc;
    font-size: 16px;
    max-width: 560px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .header-meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 32px;
    margin-top: 36px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .header-meta-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }
  .header-meta-item .label {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #6b7fc4;
  }
  .header-meta-item .value {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #cdd6f0;
  }

  /* ── MAIN LAYOUT ── */
  .main {
    max-width: 1040px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 56px 48px 80px;
  }

  /* ── SECTION HEADERS ── */
  .section-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    margin-top: 60px;
  }
  .section-header:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .section-number {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-weight: 700;
    min-width: 28px;
  }
  .section-header h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .section-header .section-sub {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-left: 4px;
  }

  /* ── RULE ── */
  .rule { height: 1px; background: var(--rule); margin: 0 0 28px; }

  /* ── PROBLEM BANNER ── */
  .problem-banner {
    background: var(--ink);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 36px 40px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .problem-banner h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #7ba7f5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-size: 11px;
  }
  .problem-banner p {
    color: #c8d0e8;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .problem-banner .divider {
    width: 1px;
    background: #2a2a4a;
    display: none;
  }

  /* ── THREE PILLARS ── */
  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .pillar {
    border: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 24px 22px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }
  .pillar-icon {
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    font-size: 17px;
  }
  .pillar h3 {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .pillar .question {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .pillar p {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* ── DESIGN SPACE ── */
  .design-space-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .design-space-item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 20px 22px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 14px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .ds-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 6px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .design-space-item h4 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .design-space-item p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .design-space-note {
    background: var(--accent-light);
    border: 1.5px solid #b8d0f8;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 18px 22px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .design-space-note p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #1a3a8a;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .design-space-note strong { font-weight: 600; }

  /* ── PRINCIPLES ── */
  .principles-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .principle-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 24px 22px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .principle-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 3px;
  }
  .principle-card.blue::before { background: var(--accent); }
  .principle-card.amber::before { background: var(--amber); }
  .principle-card.purple::before { background: var(--purple); }

  .principle-author {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .principle-card.blue .principle-author { color: var(--accent); }
  .principle-card.amber .principle-author { color: var(--amber); }
  .principle-card.purple .principle-author { color: var(--purple); }

  .principle-card h3 {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .principle-point {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 9px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .principle-point .dot {
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-top: 7px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .blue .dot { background: var(--accent); }
  .amber .dot { background: var(--amber); }
  .purple .dot { background: var(--purple); }
  .principle-point p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .principle-point strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── TENSIONS ── */
  .tensions-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .tension-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .tension-name {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .tension-side {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    line-height: 1.45;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .tension-side::before {
    content: '';
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .tension-side.a::before { background: var(--accent); }
  .tension-side.b::before { background: var(--amber); }
  .tensions-header {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 0 20px 8px;
  }
  .tensions-header span {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }

  /* ── PROCESS TIMELINE ── */
  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 40px;
  }
  .timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 11px;
    top: 8px;
    bottom: 8px;
    width: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--accent), var(--green));
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .timeline-item:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .timeline-dot {
    position: absolute;
    left: -33px;
    top: 4px;
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 2px solid white;
  }
  .timeline-dot.done { background: var(--green); }
  .timeline-dot.active { background: var(--accent); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px #b8d0f8; }
  .timeline-dot.next { background: var(--bg); border-color: var(--rule); border-width: 2px; }
  .timeline-phase {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .timeline-title {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .timeline-items-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }
  .chip {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 5px;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .chip.done { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green); }
  .chip.active { background: var(--accent-light); color: var(--accent); }
  .chip.pending { background: var(--tag-bg); color: var(--ink-light); }
  .chip::before {
    content: '';
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .chip.done::before { background: var(--green); }
  .chip.active::before { background: var(--accent); }
  .chip.pending::before { background: var(--ink-faint); }

  /* ── KEY INSIGHT CALLOUT ── */
  .key-insight {
    background: var(--ink);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin: 24px 0;
    position: relative;
  }
  .key-insight .ki-label {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: #7ba7f5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .key-insight p {
    color: #c8d0e8;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .key-insight strong { color: white; }

  /* ── DELIVERABLES ── */
  .deliverables-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .deliverable-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .deliverable-card .d-type {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .deliverable-card h4 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .deliverable-card p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .deliverable-card .status-chip {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 12px;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .status-chip.complete { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green); }
  .status-chip.in-progress { background: var(--amber-light); color: var(--amber); }

  /* ── NEXT STEPS ── */
  .next-steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 14px;
    counter-reset: steps;
  }
  .next-step {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 24px 22px;
    counter-increment: steps;
    position: relative;
  }
  .step-number {
    font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent-light);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: #c8d8fa;
  }
  .next-step h4 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .next-step p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-light);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  .footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding: 28px 48px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 1040px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 12px;
  }
  .footer span { font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }

  /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .main { padding: 40px 24px 60px; }
    .header { padding: 40px 24px 36px; }
    .header h1 { font-size: 28px; }
    .pillars, .principles-grid, .deliverables-grid, .next-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .problem-banner, .design-space-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .tension-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 8px; }
    .tensions-header { display: none; }
    .design-space-note { grid-column: 1; }
    .footer { flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; text-align: center; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- HEADER -->
<div class="header">
  <div class="header-label">System Forge · Visual Design Language</div>
  <h1>Designing a visual language for<br><span>complex systems engineering</span></h1>
  <p>Research and design work toward making SysML — a powerful but inaccessible professional language — legible, learnable, and useful without requiring weeks of training.</p>
  <div class="header-meta">
    <div class="header-meta-item"><span class="label">Phase</span><span class="value">1 of 3 · Foundations</span></div>
    <div class="header-meta-item"><span class="label">Focus</span><span class="value">SysML · Visual Design</span></div>
    <div class="header-meta-item"><span class="label">Approach</span><span class="value">Research → Principles → Visual Language</span></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="main">

  <!-- ── 01 THE PROBLEM ── -->
  <div class="section-header" style="margin-top:0">
    <span class="section-number">01</span>
    <h2>The problem <span class="section-sub">— Why this work exists</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="rule"></div>

  <div class="problem-banner">
    <div>
      <h3>What SysML is</h3>
      <p>SysML is a professional language for describing complex engineered systems — used in aerospace, automotive, defence, and infrastructure. It gives teams a shared visual vocabulary to design systems before they're built.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Why it's hard</h3>
      <p>The language was designed for language implementers, not practicing engineers. It has no learning path, no layout guidance, no progressive disclosure — and existing tools close the gap with training manuals rather than good design. The result: powerful but slow to learn and painful to use.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── 02 THE LANGUAGE ── -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">02</span>
    <h2>How SysML works <span class="section-sub">— Three questions, nine diagram types</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="rule"></div>

  <div class="pillars">
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-icon" style="background:#e8f0fd;">🧱</div>
      <h3>Structure</h3>
      <p class="question">"What is it made of?"</p>
      <p>Parts, components, ports, connections, and hierarchies. How a system is assembled and how its pieces relate to each other.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-icon" style="background:#fef3e2;">⚡</div>
      <h3>Behaviour</h3>
      <p class="question">"What does it do?"</p>
      <p>Actions, sequences, modes, transitions, and use cases. What the system does over time and in response to events.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-icon" style="background:#e4f5ed;">📋</div>
      <h3>Requirements</h3>
      <p class="question">"What must it satisfy?"</p>
      <p>Formal requirements linked directly to the design elements that must satisfy them — traceability across the whole model.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="key-insight" style="margin-top:24px;">
    <div class="ki-label">Key insight from research</div>
    <p>SysML v2 introduced one underlying pattern that unifies everything: every element is either a <strong>Definition</strong> (what a thing is) or a <strong>Usage</strong> (that thing in a specific context). This is the semantic backbone v1 never had — and it changes how the visual language can be structured.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ── 03 THE DESIGN SPACE ── -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">03</span>
    <h2>The design space <span class="section-sub">— What SysML deliberately leaves open</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="rule"></div>

  <div class="design-space-grid">
    <div class="design-space-item">
      <div class="ds-dot"></div>
      <div>
        <h4>No methodology</h4>
        <p>No guidance on where to start modeling, what order to work in, or how to decompose a complex system for the first time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-space-item">
      <div class="ds-dot"></div>
      <div>
        <h4>No layout rules</h4>
        <p>Visual arrangement is entirely up to the tool and the user. There are no defaults for where to put things or how to make diagrams readable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-space-item">
      <div class="ds-dot"></div>
      <div>
        <h4>No progressive disclosure</h4>
        <p>No guidance on what to show to whom at what level of detail. A new user and a senior engineer see exactly the same interface.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-space-item">
      <div class="ds-dot"></div>
      <div>
        <h4>No learning path</h4>
        <p>The specification is written for people implementing the language, not for engineers trying to use it. There is no onboarding, no sequence of introduction.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-space-note">
      <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-top:2px"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="9" stroke="#2d6be4" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M10 9v5M10 7h.01" stroke="#2d6be4" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      <p><strong>This is where System Forge's visual language works.</strong> The spec defines the semantics — what things mean. The design fills in everything the spec leaves blank: how the tool teaches, how it guides, how it adapts to who's using it, and how it makes the right action obvious without a manual.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ── 04 PRINCIPLES ── -->
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-number">04</span>
    <h2>Design principles <span class="section-sub">— What research contributed</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="rule"></div>

  <div class="principles-grid">
    <div class="principle-card blue">
      <div class="principle-author">Norman · Design of Everyday Things</div>
      <h3>Make the tool teach itself</h3>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Visual affordances</strong> — the way things look should reveal what can be done with them, without a manual.</p></div>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Prevent errors early</strong> — surface incompatibilities at the moment of action, not after export.</p></div>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Clear feedback</strong> — every consequential action needs an immediate, visible response.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card amber">
      <div class="principle-author">Tufte · Information Design</div>
      <h3>Reduce noise, reveal signal</h3>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Data-ink ratio</strong> — most SysML diagrams are heavily over-inked. Remove everything that doesn't carry meaning.</p></div>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Small multiples</strong> — show system views consistently across perspectives so comparison is easy.</p></div>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Layered detail</strong> — show the right level of complexity for the task at hand, not all of it at once.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card purple">
      <div class="principle-author">B2B Expert-Tool UX</div>
      <h3>Serve the professional context</h3>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Efficiency first</strong> — in long engineering sessions, every extra step is a professional cost.</p></div>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Errors have consequences</strong> — a mislabeled requirement or wrong connection can propagate through a project.</p></div>
      <div class="principle-point"><div class="dot"></div><p><strong>Multiple user types</strong> — a new engineer and a senior systems engineer may view the same model. The language must serve both.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>

