      <div class="tension-side a">Engineers expect SysML's existing notation</div>
      <div class="tension-side b">SysML notation is often cluttered and hard to read</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tension-row">
      <div class="tension-name">Precision vs. accessibility</div>
      <div class="tension-side a">Exact notation meaning must be preserved</div>
      <div class="tension-side b">Standard notation is opaque to anyone new</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tension-row">
      <div class="tension-name">Completeness vs. disclosure</div>
      <div class="tension-side a">Engineers need access to full capability</div>
      <div class="tension-side b">New users are overwhelmed by full capability</div>
    </div>
    <div class="tension-row">
      <div class="tension-name">Learnability vs. usability</div>
      <div class="tension-side a">Intuitive on first contact, forgiving</div>
      <div class="tension-side b">Fast and powerful once fluent</div>
    </div>
  </div>

